{"type":"message","id":"0f5a3ff6","parentId":"9e9d377f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T20:27:08.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Can't fetch the raw README. Let me try the Hugging Face diffusers docs for Wan training.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4HGuoaVXt81hHkTRohGL6553","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://huggingface.co/docs/diffusers/main/en/training/lora","maxChars":8000},"partialArgs":"{\"url\": \"https://huggingface.co/docs/diffusers/main/en/training/lora\", \"maxChars\": 8000}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":62,"output":101,"cacheRead":29312,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":22,"totalTokens":29475,"cost":{"input":0.00000868,"output":0.00002828,"cacheRead":0.000820736,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000857696}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780518426503,"responseId":"c3fab472-640c-4297-a5f7-6a3f628ab3ec"}}
{"type":"message","id":"55b1f048","parentId":"0f5a3ff6","timestamp":"2026-06-03T20:27:39.512Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_4HGuoaVXt81hHkTRohGL6553","toolName":"web_fetch","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"web_fetch\",\n  \"error\": \"request timed out\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"web_fetch","error":"request timed out"},"isError":true,"timestamp":1780518459510}}
{"type":"message","id":"99bd033c","parentId":"55b1f048","timestamp":"2026-06-03T20:27:45.187Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Network seems slow/spotty. Let me just answer based on what I know.\n\nFor Wan2.2 (and Wan2.1), the fine-tuning landscape is:\n\n1. **Official Wan repo** - The Wan-Video/Wan2.1 repo on GitHub includes training scripts (train.py etc.) that support LoRA fine-tuning out of the box. This is the most direct way.\n\n2. **Hugging Face Diffusers + PEFT** - Wan2.1 is officially integrated into diffusers, so you can use the diffusers training scripts with PEFT/LoRA. This is the standard approach if you're comfortable with Python scripts.\n\n3. **AI-Toolkit (formerly Kohaku)** - There's a tool called `ai-toolkit` (known as Kohaku) that has started supporting video model training including Wan.\n\n4. **ComfyUI plugins** - There are ComfyUI training nodes that can do Wan LoRA training from within ComfyUI.\n\n5. **LightX2V** - Mentioned in the Wan repo, integrates Wan2.1 and Wan2.2 but is more focused on inference optimization than training.\n\nLet me give a concise answer to 汀桑.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Wan2.2 微调目前这几条路：\n\n1. **官方 Wan 仓库** — Wan-Video/Wan2.1 自带训练脚本（train.py），LoRA 开箱即用。最直给，但得自己配环境调参。\n\n2. **Diffusers + PEFT** — Wan2.1 已合并进 Hugging Face diffusers，用 `peft` 库做 LoRA 训练。代码量少，文档齐全，适合习惯 Python 脚本的。\n\n3. **AI-Toolkit（前身 Kohaku）** — 社区工具，已经支持 Wan 系列 LoRA 训练。比官方脚本封装得好一些，但更新速度看作者心情。\n\n4. **ComfyUI 插件** — ComfyUI 有几个训练节点插件能跑 Wan LoRA，但稳定性一般，新手友好但老手嫌慢。\n\n5. **LightX2V** — Wan 官仓里提到的项目，整合了 Wan2.1 和 Wan2.2，但主要面向推理加速，训练支持有限。\n\n**我的推荐：** 想省心就官方仓库的训练脚本走一遍，想顺手就用 diffusers。你要玩 Wan2.2 的 LoRA 对吧？大概什么场景——人物一致性还是风格迁移？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":73,"output":526,"cacheRead":29440,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":251,"totalTokens":30039,"cost":{"input":0.00001022,"output":0.00014728,"cacheRead":0.00082432,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00098182}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780518459534,"responseId":"e66022b0-56b3-4502-a2b6-25bd1f34e29e"}}
