{"type":"message","id":"71179ff7","parentId":"add9d741","timestamp":"2026-06-04T06:46:00.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the problem. The \"faye-pending-urges\" cron job (which handles pushing early morning briefings and other urges) has been failing repeatedly - 7 consecutive errors. The last error was:\n\n\"session file locked (timeout 60000ms): pid=17606\"\n\nThis means the job couldn't acquire the session file lock within 60 seconds, so it timed out. This is likely a lock contention issue - another instance/process of the father agent was holding the lock.\n\nThe job is scheduled at `0 */6 * * *` (every 6 hours) with staggerMs 300000 (5 min jitter). So today it ran and errored out at every 6-hour interval.\n\nFor the early morning briefing specifically, 汀桑 has a \"/设早朝 08:00\" setup which means the briefing should trigger. Let me check how that works - the pending_urges cron is the one that's supposed to check and push urges (which would include the morning briefing). But since it keeps erroring, nothing gets pushed.\n\nLet me try to fix this issue. The lock is stale. Let me check if there's a stale lock file I can clean up.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找着了。pending-urges 那个 cron 挂了——连续 7 次报错，都是 session 文件锁超时。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_BS35OJbxHEtwdxt5l16q5419","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/ -name \"*.lock\" 2>/dev/null"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"find /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/ -name \\\"*.lock\\\" 2>/dev/null\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2511,"output":345,"cacheRead":30080,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":250,"totalTokens":32936,"cost":{"input":0.00035154,"output":0.0000966,"cacheRead":0.00084224,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00129038}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780555555932,"responseId":"12ea7969-f7a6-4263-81b4-85957745490e"}}
