{"type":"message","id":"285c289b","parentId":"12d52ebb","timestamp":"2026-06-04T06:46:12.061Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"PID 17606 is still alive - it's the main gateway process. But the lock was created at 2026-06-04T06:46:02 with maxHoldMs of 1020000 (17 minutes), and it's now much later than that. The error from the cron job said \"session file locked (timeout 60000ms): pid=17606\" for a different session (6eda55dc...). \n\nThe lock on the sessions file (c1b587f5...) is held by the main gateway process (pid 17606) which is the father agent itself. That's a legitimate lock.\n\nBut the key issue is the `pending-urges` cron is hitting lock contention. Let me look more carefully:\n\nThe cron job `faye-pending-urges` targets an isolated session. The error was for session `6eda55dc` - that's a different session from the lock I found (c1b587f5...). So the lock that caused the timeout is now gone (completed/released), but the cron job's last error was from that specific run.\n\nActually, looking closer: The cron is configured with sessionTarget \"isolated\", which means each run creates a fresh isolated session. The lock file issue happens when two processes try to use the same session file at the same time.\n\nThe stale lock file I found (c1b587f5...) is held by PID 17606 which IS the main father agent gateway process. So this is actually a different issue - the pending-urges job's session (6eda55dc) had a contention with something else.\n\nLet me check if there's a stale lock specifically for the session the cron was trying to use.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_yJEKOtAPrt00tselTZPP0740","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/ -name \"6eda55dc*\" -ls 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && ls -la /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/6eda55dc*.lock 2>/dev/null || echo \"no lock for that session\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"find /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/ -name \\\"6eda55dc*\\\" -ls 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"---\\\" && ls -la /root/.openclaw/agents/father/sessions/6eda55dc*.lock 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"no lock for that session\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":223,"output":471,"cacheRead":33024,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":357,"totalTokens":33718,"cost":{"input":0.00003122,"output":0.00013188000000000002,"cacheRead":0.000924672,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0010877719999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780555566362,"responseId":"47eabafa-2182-4f7c-aa63-21749eeee4a9"}}
