{"type":"message","id":"9c563a95","parentId":"05838682","timestamp":"2026-06-04T06:51:48.847Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me create the outbox directory and then modify the pending-urges cron payload.\n\nThe new flow:\n1. pending-urges cron runs (delivery=none), writes result to /tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json\n2. New delivery cron runs every few minutes, checks /tmp/faye-outbox/ for files, reads them, outputs the content to be announced, then deletes the file\n\nLet me first create the outbox directory, then update the pending-urges cron payload.\n\nFor the pending-urges cron, I need to update its prompt. The key changes:\n- Instead of \"创建一次性 announce cron\" to push, it should \"写文件到 /tmp/faye-outbox/xxx\"\n- The file format should be clean - just the message content and delivery info\n\nFor the new delivery cron:\n- agentId=father, isolated, delivery.mode=announce? No wait, the announce needs to target the specific user's QQ.\n- Actually, I can't set a single delivery target for all outbox files since different urges target different users.\n- I could either: a) make the delivery cron not announce but instead create announce crons for each file, or b) have one cron per user for outbox delivery.\n\nActually the simplest approach:\n- pending-urges cron writes file like `/tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json` with content `{\"to\":\"qqbot:c2c:{sender_id}\",\"accountId\":\"bot1\",\"message\":\"...\",\"channel\":\"qqbot\"}`\n- delivery cron reads all files, creates one-shot announce crons for each, deletes files\n\nLet me write the pending-urges cron payload update and create the delivery cron.\n\nActually, wait. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nThe current pending-urges cron prompt says to create a one-shot announce cron. The problem was that announce cron's output included work logs. The fix should be:\n\nFor the pending-urges flow change to outbox:\n1. It writes message content + delivery metadata to /tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json\n2. Remove the \"create announce cron\" part\n3. A separate delivery cron polls /tmp/faye-outbox/, reads each file, creates a clean one-shot cron with a precise prompt that only outputs the message content\n\nActually this is getting complex. Let me simplify:\n\n**Option A: Two-step approach**\n1. pending-urges cron → writes `/tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json`\n2. Outbox delivery cron → reads files, creates announce crons\n\nBut this still has the same problem - the announce crons could still leak work logs.\n\n**Option B: Direct file-to-announce**\n1. pending-urges cron → writes `/tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json` with `{\"message\":\"...\", \"delivery\":{...}}`\n2. Outbox delivery cron → reads files, creates a \"minimal\" announce cron that says exactly what's in the message field\n\nThe key is making the announce cron's prompt super minimal. Like:\n\"把下面这句话原样发出去，不要加任何解释：xxxxx\"\n\nBut that still runs an agent which could go off script.\n\n**Option C: Use a different delivery mechanism**\nActually, the cleanest approach would be:\n- pending-urges writes to outbox\n- delivery cron reads outbox files, and for each file, creates a **none agentTurn cron** followed by a **separate delivery announcement**... but cron doesn't work that way.\n\nHmm, actually the simplest option that avoids all agent filth:\n\nThe delivery cron reads outbox files and creates one-shot announce crons with a **minimal, locked-down prompt** that only says the exact message.\n\nLet me try this:\n\n1. Update pending-urges prompt: write to /tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json\n2. New cron \"faye-outbox-sender\": isolated agentTurn for father, every 5 min\n   - Prompt: read /tmp/faye-outbox/*.json files\n   - For each file, create a one-shot announce cron with delivery settings from the file\n   - The one-shot cron's prompt is just: \"{{message}}\" — literally just the message text\n   - OR even better: use a cron with payload kind=systemEvent and delivery\n\nWait, actually systemEvent can't do delivery. systemEvent goes to main session.\n\nLet me think differently.\n\nWhat if the outbox-sender cron itself is the one that sends? Like:\n- outbox-sender cron runs (isolated, delivery.mode=announce, targeting... wait, it targets specific users)\n- Each outbox file has different target users\n\nOK, I think the simplest approach is:\n\n1. pending-urges writes to `/tmp/faye-outbox/{sender_id}.json` (one file per urge)\n2. outbox-sender cron runs and for each file:\n   - Creates a minimal one-shot announce cron\n   - The one-shot cron's prompt is specifically crafted to just output the message without any work logs\n\nThe key improvement over the current approach is:\n- In the current approach, the announce cron prompt is generated by the pending-urges agent and can be messy\n- In the new approach, the announce cron prompt is crafted by the outbox-sender agent which reads clean data from a file\n\nActually, I think there's an even cleaner way. What if:\n\nThe outbox-sender cron creates a cron with:\n- payload: {kind: \"agentTurn\", message: \"原文转发：{{message}}\"}\n- delivery: announce to the target user\n- timeout: 30s (short, so it just sends the message)\n\nThe key is that the prompt is minimal and pre-generated, not subject to agent hallucination.\n\nLet me just implement it and see.\n\nActually, you know what's the cleanest? Write the file, then have the delivery cron:\n\n1. Read file → get message content + target\n2. Create a one-shot cron that has `sessionTarget=isolated, delivery.mode=announce, delivery.to=target, payload.message=\"你收到了一条消息：{内容}\"`\n3. The agent in that cron has nothing to do except echo the message back\n4. Delete the outbox file\n\nThe \"echo\" is the one place agent could add fluff, but with a tight prompt like \"只输出以下内容，不要加任何额外文字：{内容}\" it should be clean.\n\nOK let me just do it. Let me:\n\n1. Create outbox dir\n2. Update pending-urges cron prompt\n3. Create outbox-sender cron","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_w8TNr8zSPdFm4OeFyj686152","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mkdir -p /tmp/faye-outbox && chmod 777 /tmp/faye-outbox"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"mkdir -p /tmp/faye-outbox && chmod 777 /tmp/faye-outbox\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1278,"output":1458,"cacheRead":42112,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":1396,"totalTokens":44848,"cost":{"input":0.00017892,"output":0.00040824000000000004,"cacheRead":0.001179136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0017662959999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780555893020,"responseId":"c1f94dc2-0b0e-448a-8e3b-47ccdba4434c"}}
